      "id": "036685a3494ed6db",
      "text": "For example, in [[Visual Fox Pro]] 6, if a method named property_Assign() exists, this method fires automatically when property is modified.  If a method named property_Access() is defined, this method fires automatically when property is read.  The property_Assign() and property_Access() methods, if they exist, are responsible for completing the transaction and circularities are preempted by the class internals."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "48be5c1c456d39ef",
      "text": "Moreover, if a method named THIS_Access() is defined, this method fires for every property read, every property write, and every method call.  This_Access() should return an object instance (usually THIS) that will handle the message.  Think of this as a pre-hook for all inbound messages destined to an instance."
